<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-10-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-10-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="603" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d603">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Governor <persName type="from">Nicholls</persName>
                                to Mr. <persName type="to">Blaine</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">New
                                        Orleans, La</hi>.</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-10-28"><hi rend="italic">October 28,
                                1890</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I do not apprehend any trouble; there was for a time some excitement
                            resulting from the killing of the chief of police and the manner of his
                            taking off, but there is no occasion, and has been no occasion, for any
                            executive action or unusual action in the premises.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Francis T. Nicholls</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Governor</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>